)attr default(%+_)
  _ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>_ZCMD                                                          +
+
                                 %Rollback+
+
%Rollback+will rollback ALL changes to a specific Commit point into a new
+branch.
+
+The command will bring up a list of the last 10 commits to select from. The
+number of commits to review can be changed on the prompting panel.
+
+Each commit is avialable to be%S+selected which will browse the commit
+to allow the user to fully understand what the commit consisted of.
%
+Once a specific commit is found, use the%R+selection to initiate the
+rollback.
%
+A confirmation prompt will popup requiring the name of a new branch to be
+created AND to have the word ROLLBACK, in upper case, entered into the confirm
+entry field.
+
         +Press the%Enter+key to continue your zigi tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
)PROC
 &zup = zigih2c0
 &zcont = zigih2e0
)END
